.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATETIME.TOPLAINDATE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDateTime.toPlainDate \-
Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.toPlainDate()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toPlainDate()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object representing the date part (year,
month, day) of this date\-time in the same calendar system.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toPlainDate()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object representing the date part
(year, month, day) of this date\-time in the same calendar system.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using toPlainDate()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:34:56\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date = dt.toPlainDate();
console.log(date.toString()); \f[I]// \(aq2021\-07\-01\(aq\f[R]
.EE
